cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.NI 

This paper deals with security vulnerabilities in mobile applications, specifically related to SSL usage. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the implementation of a system in Android, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SE (Software Engineering). The system is designed to protect mobile devices, which could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The experiments conducted to assess the validity of the proposed solution involve data analysis, which could be related to cs.MA (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with mobile applications, which could be classified under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
